{{Infobox Grappling hold |name = Transition |image = Crochetage3.svg |image_size = |alt = |caption = |aka = |parent_style = Wrestling |classification = |parent_hold = |child_holds = |attacks = |counters = |escapes = }} A '''transition''' in [[grappling]] is a move from one [[grappling hold]] or [[grappling position]] to another. The process is called '''transitioning''' and is one of the most important aspects of [[grappling#Ground grappling|ground grappling]], as it allows the combatant performing the transition to advance in [[grappling position|positioning]], for instance by using a [[sweep (grappling)|sweep]], or to attempt [[grappling hold#Pinning hold|pinning holds]] or [[grappling hold#Submission hold|submission holds]].
In [[judo]], the term is also used to refer to the skillful transition between standing phase and the ground phase.
